name: Bamboozler
description: Although they might appear slow and simple, they are known to attack aggressively with quick combos of punches and kicks

name: Slobloom
description: Sloblooms are notorious for picking fights with those who deny their beauty.

name: Lunashroom
description: A Lunashroom is a solitary monster with toxic fungi on its head and back for defense. They can emit fatal nitrogenous clouds from their breath.

name: Floreen
description: Floreens move quickly through the air and disorient attackers with their stunning beauty and pollenated displays.

name: Absolopede
description: In spite of its intimidating size, Absaloms are unusually friendly even in the wild. They are prone to hugging and often refuse to let go, which can be unintentionally fatal.

name: Carathorn
description: These strange monsters pretend to be part of the forest. The Carathorn hunts via movement, so remaining calm is the best defense against its long, spiked horn and venomous gaze.

name: Terassus
description: This prehistoric monster survives through the vitality of the forest and the beauty of its flowers. It tramples anyone or anything that threatens its trees and meadows, for the Terassus bears the weight of life.

name: Turtapollen
description: The Turtapollen is a prehistoric monster that erupts with blinding and choking pollen. Its shell is harder than diamond, and it sparkles with the ancient power of the forest.

name: Vindroll
description: A stealthy, carnivorous plant that appears as a beautiful shrub. It ambushes its prey by unleashing sharp blades of grass in fierce and quick attacks.

name: Pongo
description: These powerful cyclopic monsters are able to move through the forest unnoticed. They are highly sentient and make tools and weapons with large branches.

name: Mancia
description: Mancia are usually found hanging down on jungle branches waiting to catch unsuspecting prey with their tentacle like petals

name: Buzzkill
description: The herculean Buzzkill is a knightly force unto itself, capable of rapid flight, opponents who are shown mercy often only remember a loud buzzing blur before darkness.

name: Lignicia
description: Lignicia are usually deep in the forests and camouflage so well, they are often not seen or heard, many wonder if they exist at all

name: Growilla
description: The Growilla is territorial like many other primates. Despite its size, the Growilla is very agile and will display its tremendous speed and strength if it feels threatened.

name: Tronk
description: Tronks are feral forest monsters who spend their youths in search of the perfect fighting log. Although not especially blood-thirsty, their competitiveness and athletic vigor often leads to rough housing.

name: Pumelkin
description: Pumelkins are aggressive monsters who aspire to compete in hatchy tournaments. They are easily pocketed by worthy Summoners but will fight ferociously against those it deems unworthy.

name: Shrubasaur
description: Shrubasaurs live in underground burrows and are often found in tall grass. These herbivores can change their skin color and texture to match the environment, even appearing as a leafless tree.

name: Rhynocker
description: Rhynockers dwell on the edges of forests and defend their territories with devastating charges. These large monsters will roll and lift boulders with their horns to form small caves for their young.

name: Behemoth
description: Fast, ferocious, and voracious, a Behemoth is most dangerous when pushed against the ropes. As a last resort, these monsters deploy their powerful stingers and weaken themselves to paralyze their opponents. paralyze his opponent, although this attack will leave him very weak.

name: Leaffur
description: Leaffurs travel as large families throughout the forest and defend themselves with surprising strength and courage. They are very protective of their Summoners and will often pre-emptively attack a perceived opponent

name: Boppelsmash
description: The Boppelsmash is an extremely athletic monster that jumps high in the air before crashing downward. Its impact creates small-scale tremors that can disorient its opponents.

name: Biguana
description: Groanna are very agile and have immense strength in their tail, able to send a shockwave towards an enemy

name: Kalobber
description: It might seem on the surface that this creature is very lazy and un-interesting, but it is a master of strange fighting styles, with powerful speedy blows in battle

name: Hadrowhip
description: Hadrowhips are able to shoot sharp beams of water that pierce the air and make a whipping sound

name: Psyren
description: Very shy hatchies that usually avoid humans, Wavess can sometimes be seen socializing in small groups but easily startled and lost in a body of water

name: Tentakill
description: Usually solitary, Stingta have vicious poisonous tentacles they wrap around prey to paralyze and immobilize them in the deeps

name: Clashsicle
description: Able to move quickly through ice, and can channel its water energy into a sharp spear that it uses to pierce opponents

name: Platasaur
description: Platasaur are able to blast a powerful stream of bubbles with their mouth that can knock down their target

name: Swordsnout
description: Kataspears pierce the ocean with their sharp beak-like noses and can swim great distances at top speed without tiring

name: Ramsplash
description: Ramsplash can gather enough speed and power to launch their target high into the air by ramming them

name: Jabberwelt
description: These strange Hatchies are known for their odd habit to perform a dance-like ritual to impress swimmers they admire

name: Crocodiver
description: Silent stalkers

description: Clamblast shoot off powerful beams at underwater attackers, leaving the water only to recharge in the sun, they can sometimes be seen on cliffs, pretending to be rocks

name: Frosloth
description: Frosloth are powerful frosty monsters that burrow deep into the frozen soil to hibernate, they can become very upset if woken early

name: Arcticlaw
description: Arcticlaw can be heard howling in groups while hunting, they move in packs and usually are most active at night.

name: Painguin
description: : its sharp feathers cut through any structure, it is voracious underwater, and out of the water it is beautiful to watch (from afar).

name: Krabsmack

name: Snowsquatch
description: Known for the incredible force they exert when wielding snowballs as weapons. They seem to defy gravity.

name: Diamoxius
description: The large horn of the Diamoxius strikes fear and death into all who disturb its darkness.

name: Lucifell
description: Once the brightest of Hatchies in the world, the Lucifellae lost their light and cast themselves into the shadows of the deeps.

name: Doomcade
description: Once every ten years, the Doomcadae awaken from their slumbers in the forest and emerge in dark swarms that choke the sunlight of the Sky Egg.

name: Shadarkan
description: Shadarkans are mysterious Hatchies with unclear ambitions. They enjoy riddles, tongue twisters, and obscure prophecies.

name: Noxiren
description: When Noxiren gather, their plumes of toxic gas become insurmountable and devastating. Even the most viruelent creatures avoid these noxious gatherings.

name: Toadeth
description: The slimy skin of a Toadeth is so poisonous that it inspired the vow: 'Toadeth do us part'.

name: Dreamphibian
description: The Dreamphibian uses sound and movement to hypnotize its prey into a trance like state.

name: Murcial
description: Murcials are fast and use deadly poisons they gather and trade amongst each other.

name: Leechblight
description: Leechblights are dangerous and should be avoided in the wild. When they latch onto prey, they suck the strength from their forms until pale and weak.

name: Hypnoshade
description: Hypnoshades are devious tricksters that play tricks on people for sheer amusement. It's all fun and games as long as someone loses an eye.

name: Toxiloris
description: A Toxiloris will use its large tail to launch itself on a target. A single sting from the toxic barbs on its horn causes painful paralysis and short breath.

name: Bristlebain
description: Bristlebains camouflage themselves like stones in the shade. Stepping on one of their spikes is the last wrong-step that a traveler can make.

name: Abydon
description: Abydons disappear into shadows and stalk their prey as silently as death itself.

name: Doomhopper
description: A herd of Doomhoppers is called a storm because they sound like rolling thunder across the horizon.

name: Loprogard
description: These guardians are found near the Temple of Light. Loprogards are able to sense the intentions of those who approach them.

name: Dawnclaw
description: Rising early to hunt in the twilight, a Dawnclaw cuts through the undergrowth with its razor sharp nails.

name: Pixelite
description: Pixelites spend their evenings in tall grasses and wide meadows, where they glow in fluttering dance.

name: Raydon
description: The slashing claws of a Raydon are as piercing as morning light and twice as blinding.

name: Blitzard
description: Blitzards are lightning-fast Hatchies that use their powerful tails to propel themselves away from danger or towards a meal.

name: Knightlight
description: Knightlights are fierce warriors who belong to fraternal orders. Their code demands a lifetime of sacrifice against chaos.

name: Flutterflight
description: Flutterflights are gentle and lovable Hatchies that dwell in flowerfields and grasslands. They are a favorite household friend of humans in Hatchy World.

name: Briteling
description: Considered to be extremely lucky, Britelings are sought out by humans because a simple look in their direction brings two weeks good fortune.

name: Pharoclops
description: Pharaclops are solitary Hatchies who practice the powerful arts of the third-eye. They see what most others cannot.

name: Owluminate
description: Owluminates are nocturnal creatures that can dim themselves while hunting. Once their prey is caught, however, they glow brightly to warn away other would-be scavengers.

name: Gaeltus
description: Its bronze beak and razor sharp talons make the Gaeltus a fearsome predator in the skies. Gaeltus feathers are so sharply thin that chefs use them for kitchen knives.

name: Seraph
description: Seraphs are slow-moving and sedentary in nature. Only when hungry do they move with a sense of urgency.

name: Airsupial
description: Airsupials are so light in body and mind that clouds form underneath and carry them across the vaults of the sky.

name: Skyren
description: Like their elemental cousins, the Skyrens are powerful conjurers of the energies that fill each domain.

name: Tarragonus
description: said to have been created by the primordial demigods of the Plant Hatchies, Tarragonus can summon a forest at will

name: Frostvern
description: The Frostvern forms a perpetual winter in the places they live

name: Firadra
description: Firadra have been

name: Lucirrus
description: The primordial Light Hatchy,

name: Blasilisk
description: The mighty mascot of "The Dark Elemental Spirit", The Blasilisks were equipped with deadly poison on its thorns, and toxic acid that can burn through any known material in seconds

name: Negato
description: Negatos were the first of the void dragons, created by "The Void Spirit" himself, they were gifted with the ability to seemingly bend time and space

name: Almega
description: seems to ignore rules of space and time, somehow able to know what is happening next [Alpharii can see into the near future and predict upcoming attacks.]

name: Kaiborg
description: The Kaibot are believed to be so intelligent they created themselves [The Kaiborgs promised never to return to dust, so they created new selves of metal.]

name: Badara
description: A Badaran's speed and strength are amplified in the moonlight but become weak in direct sunlight.

name: Omnipotens
description: In times of peace, they sleep in the shadows and wait. In the ends of time, they shake the heavens with pillars of white light.
